<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC6FFEAA22079D194BF09C5" pageId="15" pageNumber="1227" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC6FFEAA22079D194BF09C5" blockId="15.[809,1425,650,948]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1227">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC6FFEAA22079D193D108D1" box="[809,945,651,672]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1227">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small adult-sized, weakly muscled 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC6FFEAA22079F3938608CE" authorityName="NAEF" authorityYear="1923" box="[809,998,681,703]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1227" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cycloteuthoidea">Cycloteuthoidea</taxonomicName>
with many series of small irregular suckers on proximal manus and four series of larger suckers on distal manus; terminal pad present, with central space lacking suckers; funnel–mantle locking apparatus straight, reaching the anterior margin of the mantle; digestive gland located far posterior to the cephalic cartilage; gladius with a secondary conus; paralarvae with long retractile neck connected with a fluid-filled chamber inside the mantle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
